Underneath their graduation gowns, the Somerset Island Prep seniors wore lifejackets while riding the pristine Florida Keys waters.

Urban farmer Dan Rothschild is harvesting a stronger bond with a Manhattan soup kitchen, providing leafy greens to needy New Yorkers.

“I thought I could do a little good with minimal risk,” he said. “It feels good to be able to do something like this.”

A U.S. Open 2020 plan is in the works, including group flights, COVID tests and centralized housing.

No spectators, fewer on-court officials and no locker-room access on practice days are also being considered for reopening.
